about.description:
prompt is a library for prompting input on the command line for Python 3.3+.
It is pure Python code with no dependencies.
about.summary: Library for prompting input on the command line

name: prompt
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "prompt" %}
{% set version = "0.4.1" %}
{% set sha256 = "8a7694b88f8c65188a983315e72582bf42fcc251b97042be1d2a2ad1aa0ebe0e" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 1001
  skip: True  # [py<34]
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - pytest-runner
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - prompt

about:
  home: https://github.com/sfischer13/python-prompt
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Library for prompting input on the command line'

  description: |
    prompt is a library for prompting input on the command line for Python 3.3+.
    It is pure Python code with no dependencies.
  doc_url: http://prompt.readthedocs.io
  dev_url: https://github.com/sfischer13/python-prompt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - sfischer13
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.14
